<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1866-12-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1866-12-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="247" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d247">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Hale</persName>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 25.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi></placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1866-12-04"><hi rend="italic">December</hi> 4, 1866</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Secretary of the Navy has instructed
                            Admiral Goldsborough to send a proper national armed vessel to
                            Alexandria to receive from you John H. Surratt, a citizen of the United
                            States, who is in your custody as an arrested fugitive, charged with the
                            crime of assassination of the late Abraham Lincoln, President of the
                            United States, and of an attempt to assassinate William H. Seward,
                            Secretary of State of the United States, in the month of April, 1865.
                            You will deliver the before-named to the commanding officer of the
                            vessel upon his reporting to you his arrival at Alexandria.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Hale,</hi> Esq., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>